The paper deals with congestion problems in Multi-agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML). The paper discusses the application of state-of-the-art MARL methods for congestion problems, which falls under the sub-category of Multi-agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of difference rewards and resource abstraction, which are techniques used in Reinforcement Learning (RL), a subfield of AI and ML.
